      <crm:P4_has_time_span>
         <crm:E52_Time-span>
            <crm:P78_is_identified_by>Owner of the manuscripts was born in Diya, a small village in Enarj Enawga Waradā. He studied in different schools in the region. His expertise is in the church's music. He is one of the best oral informants in the region. He is the best expert in oral traditions about the history of the church and the country. Now he is serving as the head of the Falaga Bǝrhan Iyasus. He has "never taught Andǝmta but purchased the copied manuscripts from a 'certain farmer from a nearby village called 'Ambager'."</crm:P78_is_identified_by>
         </crm:E52_Time-span>
